==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strike zone
<hw>Strike" zone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Baseball)</fld>
<def>the area above home plate where, if a pitched ball passes through
and is not hit by the batter, the pitch counts as a strike.
Specifically, it is directly above home plate and at a height from the
knees to the shoulders of the batter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Striking</ent>⟦br⟧
